<CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: (Bob Marley Celebration)  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  ENTERTAINMENT  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  The Bob Marley Celebration and Jamaican Cultural Festival commemorates the
life and music of reggae's best-known legend.;    Two concerts are scheduled,
one in Berkeley on Sunday and the other in Santa Cruz on Monday.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  MARLEY CELEBRATIONS  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Entertainment  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Sunday's concert is at 4 p.m. at the Berkeley Community Theatre, 1900
Allston Way. ASWAD (Tony Gad, Angus Zeb and Brinsley Forde, above), England's
leading reggae group, will appear, along with Judy Mowatt, Joe Higgs and Della
Grant.;    The Monday performance is scheduled for 7 p.m. at the Santa Cruz
Civic Auditorium, 307 Church St. In addition to ASWAD and Judy Mowatt, it
features Square Roots.;    In celebration of Jamaican culture, a number of
Northern California artists will be exhibiting and selling their crafts at
both shows.;    Admission to each concert is $18.50. For tickets, call (415)
762-2277 or (408) 998-2277. For crafts booth information, call (415)
541-0800.;    (box) THEATER: "Lift Every Voice" celebrates Black history at
the Lorraine Hansberry Theater. February is Black History Month. Shown at 2
and 8 tonight, 2 p.m. Sunday and 8 p.m. Wednesday-next Friday, Hansberry
Theater, 620 Sutter St., San Francisco. $15-$22. Through Feb. 24. For more
information, call (415) 474-8800.;    (box) ART: At San Jose State University
Art Gallery is an exhibit of paintings by Steve Bronson, through March 7. 11
a.m.-4 p.m. Mondays-Thursdays; 6-8 p.m. Tuesdays. Art Building, San Jose State
University, near Ninth and San Carlos streets, San Jose. (408) 924-4328.  </TEXT>
